@NODE "FEATURES" "Features"
@TOC "MAIN"

 @{b}Features
 ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{ub}

 SortMail lets you search incoming mail for messages containing configured
 addresses, user names, subjects, etc.  Once a message is found, SortMail
 can do one or more of the following:

   · Copy or move it to another conference

   · Save it to disk

   · If it is a digest; split it into seperate messages

   · If it is an Aminet RECENT listing; parse it into the filebase and/or
     display a list of new files in the New Files window

   · Execute external ARexx scripts.  A script for running executables is
     included

 Possible uses for SortMail include sorting mailing list messages into
 seperate conferences, moving messages from certain persons into their own
 conference, maintaining an index of files available on AmiNet and saving
 messages from mailing bots to disk.

 Through the use of external ARexx scripts you can also add new functions
 yourself.

 SortMail will also write log messages addressed to the user with warnings
 and errors that occured while processing the messages, information from the
 AmiNet RECENT messages and optionally statistics on SortMail's doings.
 
 In other words it is not of any use for people without an Internet Email
 address.


 What's new in 3.0?
 @{b}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{ub}

 Everything.  SortMail has been completely rewritten.  This also means the
 configuration format has changed.  If you have used previous version of
 SortMail, you will have to configure it again.  I'm sorry, but for several
 reasons no conversion script has been made.

 Users of older versions are recommended to browse through SortMail.guide to
 familiarize themselves with the new trigger based message processing system.

@ENDNODE

