@NODE "L2EMAIL" "Local2Email.br"
@TOC "Main"
 
 @{b}Local2Email.br
 ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{ub}

 The idea for Local2Email.br was taken from ML2Email.thor by Remco van
 Hooff.  When run it will go through the active unpacked events and do the
 following:

 · Replace NOT_ON_BBS (local) conference names with the name of the Email
   conference and add the reply address configured in CfgSortMail to the
   list of recievers.  If there is no reply address configured both
   conference name and to address will be left alone

   NOT_ON_BBS conferences are usually created by SortMail.  Local2Email
   will not replace names of conferences not present in Thor's database, so
   you can safely post messages to newsgroups you are not a member of.

 · Check if the to-address equals a name in the user database.  If it does
   it will try to replace the name with the corresponding address(es) from
   the user database.  This will only work with one single name

   Note:  If the name contains any wildcard characters (#, ?, *, | or
   parathentises) or a @, then the name will not be replaced

 In short it will allow you to forget about specifying the correct email
 conference and reciever's address when entering messages or replying to
 messages SortMail has copied to conferences only existant internally in
 Thor's message database.

 Be aware that Local2Email.br won't issue any warnings if it fails to do
 any of the above.  So in order for this script to run properly, make sure
 you have configured a reply address for each mailing list conference you
 have configured.

 Local2Email.br supports crossposting to any kind of conference as long as
 they are on the same system.

 You can also use Local2Email.br to create a simple mailing list.  Check out
 @{" Hints and tips " LINK "HINT"} for the hot details.


 Running Local2Email.br
 @{b}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{ub}

 Local2Email.br can be run both from Thor and from the Shell.  When run from
 Thor it is best to run it when leaving the system containing your Email
 conference. To do this select Local2Email.br in the "Leaving system" string
 gadged in ConfigThor -> System Configuration -> @{" Files/Paths window " ALINK "ConfigTHOR.guide/Files-Paths"}.

 If you have a special script grabbing mail for you, you might want to run
 it before uploading messages instead.  Add a line like this:

    rx `GetEnv THOR/THORPATH`rexx/Local2Email.br "<system name>"

 to the script, replacing <system name> with the name of the system
 containing your Email conference.

 Local2Email.br requires that a configuration file for SortMail 3.0 or
 higher has been created.  A reply address will have to be created for each
 mailing list and/or digest in order to guarantee that Local2Email will find
 the correct address.
 

 Command template
 @{b}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{ub}

 Usage      rx Local2Email.br SYSTEM <system>

 Template   SYSTEM/A

 Arguments  SYSTEM/A should be clear enough

 Example    rx Local2Email.br SYSTEM "News&Mail"

@ENDNODE

@NODE "HISTORY" "History"
@TOC "Main"

 @{b}History
 ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{ub}

 3.35 (3.3.97)
 @{b}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{ub}

 New   · The New Files listing is automatically sorted by directory
       · No warnings about empty RECENT message anymore. Also, the
         list of new files is deleted when an empty RECENT is found

 Fixed · Fixed problems with last file in RECENT not getting added that some
         people had
       · Online help didn't always go to the correct node in SortMail.guide
       · Save message didn't write the Reply-To: line
       · Local2Email would sometimes not change the conference name to
         EMail
       · Saving messages to disk didn't work if there was a space in the
         destination path


 3.34 (27.10.96)
 @{b}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{ub}

 Fixed  · Some digest may have been "swallowed" by SortMail if they
          contained MIME base64 attachments


 3.33 (15.10.96) @{i}internal@{ui}
 @{b}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{ub}

 New    · Added support for message forwarding in Local2Email

 Fixed  · CfgSortMail and SortMail.guide said users are always added from
          messages in the Email conference, which is not true
        · Prevented some busy loops that could occur if the configuration
          file was invalid
        · If user adding is turned off for the system in ConfigThor, then
          SortMail will never try to delete users. This will give a small
          speed increase on some configurations


 3.32 (22.9.96) @{i}internal@{ui}
 @{b}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{ub}

 New    · SHANGHAI/S will now always be able to get the list of unread
          messages with Thor 2.4 or newer. Previously SortMail could only
          get it from the system active in Thor
        · Updates conference window only if messages were processed

 Fixed  · Digest parser has been made slightly more compatible with "weird"
          digest formats
        · Local2Email would sometimes mess up events if there was a user
          without an address in the user database


 3.31 (3.9.96)
 @{b}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{ub}

 New    · If SortMail is using a Thor ARexx port the name is available as
          an ARexx clip ('SM_ThorPort')
        · RunCommand.br is updated to use the SM_ThorPort clip

 Fixed  · Save message would always report it failed when SortMail was run
          from the Shell without the SHANGHAI switch, even if it didn't
        · If an exclude file was used for RECENT messages files would never
          be added to the file database
        · Non-MIME digests with only one sub-message would cause an error
        · The installer would fail if ENV:THOR/THORPATH did not have a
          linefeed and reported wrong path in the exit window


 3.3 (24.8.96)
 @{b}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{ub}

 New    · Support for multiple systems
        · SYSTEM is now a required argument when running SortMail from Shell
        · RECENT parser can be configured to disable adding of MOTD & stats
        · RECENT parser now supports exclusion of both parent and child dirs
        · Local2Email.br now has proper support for crossposting and
          multiple recipients
        · Wrote an Installer script

 Fixed  · When two entries in a list had the same name the first one would
          always be selected.  Worked around this by numbering the entries
        · Local2Email would sometimes spread data for one event onto others.
          Also improved the general behaviour
        · RECENT messages with no new files listed could cause trouble
        · A few minor quirks here and there


 3.2 (8.7.96)
 @{b}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{ub}

 New    · It's now possible to specify a destination system for copied
          messages and splitted digests
        · The RECENT parser now lets you decide whether to add the files to
          the file database or not.  If not, the files will only be shown in
          the New Files window.  Might be useful on slower machines

 Fixed  · Further improvements and fixes in digest splitter
        · Local2Email didn't replace local conference names on replies

 3.1 (14.6.96)
 @{b}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{ub}

 New    · SortMail can now be forced to match all search criterias in a
          trigger.  Default: only one match required
        · More info is shown in trigger listview
        · Made it possible to rearrange triggers in CfgSortMail

 Fixed  · Saving of messages would fail if the NOBIN switch was used 
        · KEYWORD would appear in the cfg file even when it wasn't used
        · Reply address wasn't always properly set when parsing digests
        · Local2Email.br would fail on crosspostings.  Thanks to Andreas
          Baum for fixing this one
        · Improved non-MIME digest splitting a bit


 3.0 (24.5.96)
 @{b}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{ub}
 
 New    · Completely rewritten
        · New trigger based configuration system
        · Execution of external scripts
        · Saves messages to disk
        · Splits MIME multipart messages (commonly used for digests)
        · Digest splitting no longer requires you to configure a
          "end-of-digest" line, SortMail will find it itself
        · New and more intuitive CfgSortMail
        · Can be run both from Thor and the Shell command line
        · Renamed to SortMail.br since it no longer requires Thor to run
        · Uudecoding removed since it is now automatically done by Thor
        · ...and a whole lot more


 1.0 - 2.3a
 @{b}ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ@{ub}

 Ancient history

